article.headline: Florida A&amp,M 69, Allen 36
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- Yannick Crowder scored 15 points to lead Florida A&M over Allen 69-36 on Monday night. Crowder was 6 of 7 shooting as the Rattlers (5-5) made 41.5 percent from the field (27 of 65). The Yellow Jackets, of the NAIA, made just 11 of their 49 shots (22.4 percent), helping lead to an overwhelming rebounding advantage for Florida A&M. Christopher Walker grabbed 10 rebounds as the Rattlers held a 59-29 edge on the boards. Florida A&M also held a 14-6 edge in assists, with Rasheem Jenkins dishing out four. Amir Stevens chipped in 10 points for the Rattlers. Demetrice Terrell was the only scorer in double figures for Allen with 11 points. Terrell was 3 of 9 from 3-point range, as the Yellow Jackets shot 4 of 19 from behind the arch (21.1 percent).
